svg.title: A diagram of a horizontal gas pipe with three taps. Tap A is located towards the right where the pipe meets the wall. Its handle is vertical, and it is labelled “turned on.” Tap B is located on the left end of the pipe where it turns upwards. Its handle is horizontal, and it is labelled “turned off.” Between the two, a flexible tube connects to the pipe and leads away to a lamp. Tap C is located on this branch. Its handle is horizontal, and it is labelled “turned on.”
